parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Ignition Switch Failure and Electrical Fires
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ignition switch can cause electrical fires, which can lead to vehicle damage, injury, or even fatalities.
symptoms: The ignition switch snaps or fails
causing a fire while the vehicle is in motion or parked
smoke coming from the steering column
smoke coming from under the hood
flames shooting from under the hood
electrical wiring shorts
and instrument panel wiring burning out.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The TFI module overheating can cause the vehicle to stall, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle stalls due to the TFI module overheating
which is often caused by the module being placed too close to the engine.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of dashboard lights can cause difficulty in monitoring vehicle systems, leading to potential safety issues.
symptoms: The dashboard lights fail
causing a lack of visibility and awareness of vehicle systems.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunction of the seat belt buckle can cause the seat belt to become unlatched or stuck, leaving the driver or passenger unrestrained, which can increase the risk of injury or death in the event of an accident.
symptoms: The seat belt buckle sticks or jams
the seat belt comes unlatched while driving
the seat belt buckle button breaks off
the seat belt twists or retracts
becoming jammed
the seat belt fails to latch or remain latched.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Corrosion on the brake rotor can lead to reduced braking performance, increasing the stopping distance and risk of accidents.
symptoms: Rusted or corroded brake rotors
uneven brake wear
grinding or screeching noise when applying the brakes.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Failure of the brake system can cause the vehicle to lose braking ability, leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: Popping noise when pressing the brakes
loud noise from the brake system
inability to stop the vehicle
brake pedal feels soft or spongy.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A stuck accelerator pedal can cause the vehicle to accelerate unintentionally, leading to loss of control and accidents.
symptoms: Gas pedal stuck
unable to slow down or stop the vehicle
vehicle accelerates unexpectedly.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the TFI ignition module can cause the vehicle to stall suddenly, leading to a loss of power and control, which can increase the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The vehicle stalls without warning
the vehicle stalls repeatedly
the engine shuts off while driving
the vehicle may restart after stalling.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ignition switch can cause the electrical system to malfunction, leading to a loss of power and control, which can increase the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The instrument panel goes out
the radio turns off
the vehicle shuts off while driving
the vehicle may restart after shutting off.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the automatic transmission can cause the vehicle to lose power and control, leading to a loss of vehicle speed and acceleration, which can increase the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The transmission fails to fully engage into indicated gears
the transmission slips or hesitates
the transmission indicator shows the wrong gear
the shoulder strap refuses to engage.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the catalytic converter can cause the vehicle to experience poor engine performance, reduced fuel efficiency, and increased emissions, which can lead to costly repairs and environmental harm.
symptoms: The catalytic converter needs to be replaced repeatedly
the vehicle experiences poor engine performance
the vehicle experiences reduced fuel efficiency.
